Defects
Defects refer to flaws or shortcomings identified from real user experiences.

Selling Point
Selling Point refers to advantages or attractive features identified from real user experiences.

Honda Wave 110i
Honda Wave 110i is recommended for Rider Delivery due to its fast return on investment.

Yamaha Finn
Yamaha Finn is suggested for Rider Delivery because it has a 5-year warranty and can withstand rough usage.

Honda Lead 125
Honda Lead 125 is an utility scooter with a large U-box storage, fuel tank located at the front, but has slippery tires on wet roads and lacks a console box for storage.<SEP>Honda Lead 125 is recommended for Rider Delivery who prefer comfort due to its ease of storage and quick fueling.

Yamaha Fazzio
Yamaha Fazzio is suggested for University Students on a budget or those seeking a cute design.

Grand Filano
Grand Filano is a motorcycle that competes with Honda Giorno+, and it has less storage space under the seat compared to Lead 125 and Grand Filano.<SEP>Grand Filano is another option for University Students who want to save money or prefer a cute design.

Honda Giorno+
Honda Giorno+ is a motorcycle with a stronger engine (eSP+ 4 valve water-cooled) compared to competitors, positioned for young enthusiasts who like customization.<SEP>Honda Giorno+ targets the market against Grand Filano with a stronger engine and is positioned as a fashionable option for youth.<SEP>Honda Giorno+ is recommended for University Students looking for performance.

PCX 160
PCX 160 is suggested for Office Workers and University Students due to its comfort and performance.<SEP>PCX 160 is a motorcycle model included in the cost analysis for maintenance and ownership.

NMAX 155
NMAX 155 is recommended for Office Workers as it allows easy maneuvering and efficient commuting.<SEP>NMAX 155 is a motorcycle model included in the cost analysis for maintenance and ownership.

Honda ADV 160
A Honda scooter model with enhanced suspension and ground clearance.<SEP>Honda ADV 160 is suggested for areas with poor road conditions or frequent flooding due to its robust suspension and deep water capability.

Active Safety
Active Safety refers to the enhanced safety features in larger engine capacity scooters, emphasizing better acceleration and overtaking capabilities.

Showa Suspension
Rear suspension by Showa, equipped with a sub-tank to prevent cavitation when the suspension is heavily used.<SEP>Showa Suspension is highlighted for its smooth ride quality on ADV models.

Storage Space Under Seat
Storage space under the seat refers to additional storage capacity, with XMAX offering room for two helmets compared to NMAX's single helmet storage.

Rider Delivery
Rider Delivery refers to individuals who deliver food or packages using motorcycles.

University Student
University Student refers to students enrolled in a university, often needing reliable transportation for their daily commute.

Office Worker
Office Worker refers to employees who work in an office environment and may require commuting for their job.

Heavy Duty/Flooded Area
Heavy Duty/Flooded Area refers to regions with poor road conditions or frequent flooding, necessitating durable transportation.

Showa
Showa is a company known for producing rear shock absorbers with sub-tanks.

SYM
SYM is a leading scooter brand from Taiwan, collaborating on the development of engines like those used in GPX Drone 150.<SEP>A leading scooter brand from Taiwan that collaborates on the development of GPX Drone 150.

Honda Forza 350
Honda Forza 350 is a maxi-scooter with an eSP+ engine and electric windshield that can be adjusted up to 180 mm.

Yamaha XMAX 300
Yamaha XMAX 300 is a maxi-scooter featuring dual clamp front forks and optional Y-Connect & Garmin Navigation on Tech Max models.

Yamaha R15M
Yamaha R15M is a sport motorcycle equipped with features such as an assist and slipper clutch and quick shifter (on some models).<SEP>Yamaha R15M is a sport motorcycle equipped with assist and slipper clutch, quick shifter, and has maintenance issues like USD fork leaks and expensive tires.

MT-15
MT-15 is a naked bike variant by Yamaha, featuring tech advancements like the assist and slipper clutch.<SEP>MT-15 is a motorcycle model that shares the same assist and slipper clutch feature as Yamaha R15M but lacks the quick shifter.

GPX Drone 150
GPX Drone 150 is a scooter developed with SYM that offers value at a lower price point compared to PCX/NMAX.

PCX
PCX is a competitor of GPX Drone 150 in terms of market positioning and pricing.

NMAX
NMAX is a competitor of GPX Drone 150 in terms of market positioning and pricing.

Electric Windshield
The Electric Windshield is an adjustable windshield on the Honda Forza 350 that can be raised up to 180 mm.

Clutch Noise
Clutch Noise refers to the sound and vibration issues experienced in Honda Forza 350 clutches that require maintenance or replacement.

Water Pump Leak
Water Pump Leak refers to the leakage issues found in Honda Forza 350 water pumps, typically affecting high-mileage vehicles.

Rear Mirror Vibration
Rear Mirror Vibration refers to the shaking of mirrors in Honda Forza 350, making it difficult to see behind clearly at high speeds.

Oil Consumption
Oil Consumption refers to the high oil usage in Yamaha XMAX 300 engines, necessitating regular oil level checks.<SEP>Oil consumption refers to the symptom of engine oil depletion, a common issue for Tech Max requiring frequent dipstick checks.

Seat Height
Seat Height refers to the high and wide seating position in Yamaha XMAX 300 that can make it hard for shorter riders to control the vehicle while stationary.

Quick Shifter
A Quick Shifter is an advanced tech feature in the Yamaha R15M that enables seamless gear shifting.

Dual Clamp Front Fork
Dual Clamp Front Fork is an engineering feature in Yamaha XMAX 300 that enhances stability during cornering or heavy braking.

Assist & Slipper Clutch
An Assist & Slipper Clutch is a tech feature in both the Yamaha R15M and MT-15 that prevents rear wheel lock-up during downshifts.

Y-Connect & Garmin Navigation
Y-Connect & Garmin Navigation is a feature on Yamaha XMAX 300 Tech Max models, providing full navigation maps on the TFT display.

Keyless System
Keyless System is a feature in GPX Drone 150 that sometimes fails to find signals or malfunctions.

Sensor Issues
Sensor Issues refer to problems with the side stand switch in GPX Drone 150 that can prevent the vehicle from starting.

Cooling System
Cooling System refers to the problem of coolant leakage in GPX Drone 150 that requires regular checks on hose clamp connections.

Ground Clearance
Ground Clearance refers to the height of the vehicle from the ground, measured as 165 mm for Honda Forza 350.<SEP>The ground clearance of ADV 160 is 165 mm, higher than PCX to allow better performance in flooded areas or on sidewalks.

Ride Height
Ride Height refers to the measurement of vehicle height from the ground, such as the 165 mm clearance on Honda Forza 350.

Windscreen
Adjustable windscreen in two height levels for ADV 160 model.<SEP>Windscreen is an adjustable feature on Honda Forza 350 and GPX Drone 150, allowing adjustment to two levels for rider comfort.

Technical Benefit
Technical Benefit refers to the advantage of separating oil and gas in rear shock absorbers with sub-tanks, preventing cavitation.

Sub-Tank Shock Absorber
A Sub-Tank Shock Absorber is a type of rear shock absorber with additional tanks to separate oil and gas, enhancing performance.

Cavitation Prevention
Cavitation Prevention is a technical benefit of using sub-tank shock absorbers that helps maintain performance under heavy use.

Rear Shock Absorber
A Rear Shock Absorber is a component of suspension systems that helps absorb impacts and maintain vehicle stability.

Suspension System
Suspension System refers to the components of a vehicle that absorb impacts and maintain stability, including rear shock absorbers with sub-tanks by Showa.

Maxi-Scooter
Maxi-Scooter refers to the category of large-capacity scooters designed for long-distance touring, such as Honda Forza 350 and Yamaha XMAX 300.

Touring Scooter
Touring Scooter refers to a type of scooter suitable for long journeys with comfort and power, such as Honda Forza 350 and Yamaha XMAX 300.

Dual Clamp Front Forks
Dual Clamp Front Forks are an engineering feature on Yamaha XMAX 300 that enhance stability during cornering or heavy braking.

TFT Display
A TFT Display is a technology used on the Yamaha XMAX 300 Tech Max model to show full navigation maps.

Tech Features
Tech Features refer to advanced technical elements integrated into vehicles like the quick shifter and assist & slipper clutch in Yamaha R15M/MT-15.

Engine Specs
Engine Specs refer to detailed specifications of a vehicle's engine, including displacement and valve count like those found in Honda Forza 350.

Performance Characteristics
Performance Characteristics refer to specific performance metrics of vehicles, like torque and rpm ranges in Honda Forza 350.

Signature Feature
Signature Feature refers to a distinctive or unique feature of a vehicle model, such as the electric windshield on Honda Forza 350.

Chassis Engineering
Chassis Engineering refers to the design and build of a vehicle's frame, including the dual clamp front forks on Yamaha XMAX 300.

Key Features
Key Features refer to the main features or highlights of a vehicle model like Y-Connect & Garmin Navigation on Yamaha XMAX 300 Tech Max models.

Common Defects
Common Defects refer to frequent issues or problems experienced with a particular model, such as oil consumption and seat height in Yamaha XMAX 300.<SEP>Common Defects refer to typical issues that affect motorcycles, such as hard shifting and vibration.

Torque Master
Torque Master refers to the Honda Forza 350's capability of delivering high torque at low rpm levels, making acceleration easier.

Market Selloff
Market Selloff refers to significant declines in stock values due to investor concerns over interest rates and regulations, which was not applicable here but mentioned as a concept for completeness.

Crankshaft
The crankshaft uses a Roller Bearing (roller bearing) on the right side to reduce friction and engine vibration.

Piston Oil Jet
A fuel jet under the piston similar to Wave 125i.<SEP>The Piston Oil Jet technology involves oil jets under the piston to lubricate the engine, improving efficiency.

CVT Judder
Shaking during acceleration (0-20 km/h) caused by dust accumulation in the clutch housing, resolved by blowing out dust or replacing the carbon clutch cloth.

Oil Pump Gear Failure
Failure of the oil pump gear made from composite plastic, leading to insufficient lubrication and engine seizure if using excessively thick oil or sudden jerks.

eSAF (Enhanced Smart Architecture Frame)
A lightweight chassis frame produced from stamped steel but has concerns about rust and long-term strength in some production lots.

Yamaha NMAX 155
A Yamaha scooter model featuring Blue Core VVA engine technology.

Aerox 155
Another Yamaha scooter model featuring Blue Core VVA engine technology.

VVA (Variable Valve Actuation)
Intelligent variable valve actuation system with two intake rocker arms, one for low and mid-range RPMs and another for high RPMs above 6,000 rpm to increase airflow and maintain power.

Forged Piston
A forged piston similar to that used in the R1 sports bike model, providing strength and lighter weight than cast pistons.

Code 12 (Aerox/Lexi)
Issues with stator coil terminals melting due to heat accumulation, leading to poor electrical flow, preventing the vehicle from starting or shutting off unexpectedly.

Stiff Suspension
Rigid rear suspension on NMAX models causing a stiff ride when driving solo; Aerox models are slightly more comfortable.

Tensioner Failure
Failure of the chain tensioner in older models leading to noisy engine operation.

GPX Drone 150 (4-Valve)
A four-valve scooter model developed in collaboration with SYM, priced lower than PCX/NMAX by approximately 15,000 - 20,000 Thai Baht.

Spiny Sleeve
The Spiny Sleeve is a type of carbon-fiber spike designed to enhance grip and heat dissipation.

Hard Shifting
Hard Shifting refers to difficulties in shifting gears, particularly from 1st to 2nd gear when the engine is cold.

Vibration
Vibration describes the tendency for an engine to shake or vibrate, especially as it ages.

Fuel Economy
Fuel Economy refers to the efficiency of fuel consumption, measured at 71.4 km/liter.<SEP>Fuel Economy refers to the high fuel efficiency of Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid, achieving up to 60-65 km/liter.

Yamaha Finn 115
A motorcycle offering a standout warranty of 5 years unlimited mileage and flex-fuel capabilities with E85 support in some variants.<SEP>The Yamaha Finn 115 is a motorcycle that offers a five-year warranty and flex fuel capability.

Honda Wave
The Honda Wave is a motorcycle known for its ride comfort, especially when encountering bumps.

Unified Brake System (UBS)
The Unified Brake System automatically activates the front brake when the rear brake is applied, improving braking efficiency.

Suzuki Raider R150
The Suzuki Raider R150 is a 150cc motorcycle marketed as "King of Underbone," with advanced engineering specifications and design features.

Engine (147.3 cc DOHC 4 Valves)
This engine type in the Suzuki Raider R150 utilizes dual overhead camshafts for high performance, peaking at 18.5 PS at 10,000 rpm.

Suzuki Advanced Twin Spar Frame
The Suzuki Advanced Twin Spar Frame is a frame design inspired by big bikes like the GSX-R, providing strength to handle high torque.

Honda PCX 160 & Click 160
The Honda PCX 160 and Click 160 are motorcycles that use eSP+ 4 Valves engine technology for improved air intake and exhaust efficiency.

Roller Bearing Crankshaft
A crankshaft with roller bearings is used to reduce friction and smooth out the engine operation in Honda PCX 160 & Click 160 motorcycles.

Honda PCX 160
The Honda PCX 160 is a premium scooter with eSP+ engine technology offering high performance and efficiency.

Click 160
The Click 160 is a premium scooter with eSP+ engine technology providing improved air intake and exhaust efficiency.

Tech Max
Tech Max is a motorcycle model with advanced features such as a full navigation map display on the TFT screen.

Kawasaki Ninja 400
Kawasaki Ninja 400 has a 399 cc parallel twin engine, requires major service every 24,000 km with high maintenance costs and experienced clutch slippage in models from 2018-2019.

Kawasaki ZX-25R
Kawasaki ZX-25R is a motorcycle model equipped with a 4-cylinder engine and requires expensive spark plugs and high-cost valve clearance maintenance.

Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid
Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid uses Blue Core Hybrid technology with an SMG (Smart Motor Generator) that assists power delivery for smoother acceleration and better fuel economy up to 60-65 km/liter, but has a maximum speed limit of approximately 100-105 km/h.<SEP>Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid features Blue Core Hybrid technology, uses an SMG motor to assist power delivery during acceleration, offers excellent fuel economy but has limited top speed.

Seat Height Issue
The seat height issue on Tech Max makes it difficult for shorter riders to place their feet fully flat on the ground while parked.

USD Fork Leak
USD Fork Leak refers to issues with the inverted forks leaking sealant easily if damaged by debris, a common maintenance issue in Yamaha R15M.

Tire Cost Issue
Tire Cost Issue refers to the expensive rear tire for Yamaha R15M, priced between 2,000-3,500 baht per piece.

Clutch Slippage Issue
Clutch Slippage Issue refers to the problem of weak clutch springs causing slippage during heavy use in Kawasaki Ninja 400 models from 2018-2019.

Spark Plug Cost Issue
Spark Plug Cost Issue refers to the high cost of spark plugs for Kawasaki ZX-25R, priced between 400-600 baht per plug.

Valve Clearance Maintenance Issue
Valve Clearance Maintenance Issue refers to the high labor costs associated with setting valve clearance on Kawasaki ZX-25R due to its four-cylinder engine.

Wet Road Slippery Tires
Wet Road Slippery Tires refers to the issue where Honda Lead 125 tires become extremely slippery on wet roads.

Lack of Console Box
Lack of Console Box refers to the absence of a console box for storage on Honda Lead 125.

Market Competition Against Grand Filano
Market Competition Against Grand Filano refers to the competitive positioning of Honda Giorno+ against the Grand Filano.

Limited Storage Under Seat
Limited Storage Under Seat refers to the smaller storage space under the seat compared to Lead 125 and Grand Filano.

Hybrid Motor Assistance
Hybrid Motor Assistance refers to the use of an SMG motor in Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid to aid power delivery during acceleration.

Limited Top Speed
Limited Top Speed refers to the restricted maximum speed of Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid at around 100-105 km/h.

Blue Core Hybrid
Blue Core Hybrid is the technology used in Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid that incorporates an SMG (Smart Motor Generator) for improved power delivery and fuel efficiency.

Wave 110i/125i
Wave 110i/125i is a motorcycle model included in the cost analysis for maintenance and ownership.

Lead 125
Lead 125 is a motorcycle model compared to other models in terms of storage space under the seat.

Forza 350
Forza 350 is a motorcycle model included in the cost analysis for maintenance and ownership.

XMAX 300
XMAX 300 is a motorcycle model included in the cost analysis for maintenance and ownership.

Ninja 400
Ninja 400 is a motorcycle model included in the cost analysis for maintenance and ownership.

Sport 400
Sport 400 is a motorcycle model included in the cost analysis for maintenance and ownership.

Vespa 150 (Sprint)
Vespa 150 (Sprint) is a motorcycle model included in the cost analysis for maintenance and ownership.

data.content:
Comprehensive Motorcycle Knowledge Base Thailand Market (2024-2026)
A knowledge base consolidating data on motorcycles in the Thai market from 2024 to 2026, including engineering specs, defect analysis, maintenance costs, and sales strategy.

Honda Wave 110i (2024-2025)
A motorcycle model in the family and underbone segment known for its fuel efficiency and durability, featuring a Honda Smart Engine with an undersquare design to enhance torque at low RPMs.

Honda Wave 125i
A motorcycle model equipped with key technologies such as Piston Oil Jet, Hydraulic Chain Tensioner, and Spiny Sleeve, aimed at reducing wear and maintenance costs while providing improved fuel economy.

Family & Underbone Segment
A segment of motorcycles focused on affordability, durability, and low maintenance costs, crucial for transportation in Thailand.

Engineering Specs
A category of data detailing technical specifications such as engine size, architecture, and performance outcomes.

Defect Analysis
An analysis that identifies common defects and issues in motorcycles like the Honda Wave 110i and Honda Wave 125i.

Maintenance Costs
A category of data detailing the costs associated with maintaining various components of motorcycles, such as engine oil, spark plugs, air filters, and brake pads.

Sales Strategy
A strategy for selling motorcycles that includes unique selling points like warranties and fuel flexibility.

125cc Scooter Upgrade
The concept of Active Safety is highlighted when upgrading from a 125cc scooter to a 160cc scooter, emphasizing enhanced safety during acceleration and overtaking.

ADV Scooters
Showa Suspension enhances the ride quality of ADV scooters by providing a smoother experience.

XMAX 160
The storage space under the seat in XMAX 160 is larger compared to NMAX 155, allowing for two helmet storage instead of one.

Maxi-Sport
The Honda Forza 350 belongs to the category of maxi-scooters designed for long-distance touring.

Roller Bearing
The crankshaft uses a roller bearing to reduce friction and vibration.

Wave 125i
A fuel jet under the piston is similar to that of Wave 125i.

Excessively Thick Oil
Failure of the composite plastic oil pump gear may occur if excessively thick oil is used or sudden jerks are applied to the engine.

Clutch Cloth Accumulation
Shaking during acceleration due to dust accumulation in the clutch housing can be resolved by cleaning or replacing the carbon clutch cloth.

Chassis
The lightweight chassis frame is made from stamped steel but has concerns about rust and long-term strength in some production lots.

TFT Screen
Tech Max is equipped with a full navigation map display on the TFT screen.

Parallel Twin Engine
Kawasaki Ninja 400 is powered by a 399 cc parallel twin engine delivering 45 horsepower.

Four-Cylinder Engine
Kawasaki ZX-25R is engineered with a 4-cylinder engine that reaches redline at 17,000 rpm.

Blue Core Hybrid Technology
Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid utilizes Blue Core Hybrid technology featuring an SMG motor to aid power delivery for smoother acceleration and better fuel economy.

U-Box Storage
Honda Lead 125 boasts the largest U-box storage in its class with a volume of 37 liters.

Major Service
Kawasaki Ninja 400 requires major service every 24,000 km with significant costs for valve setting, spark plug replacement, and fluid changes.

Speed Limitation
Yamaha Grand Filano Hybrid's maximum speed is limited to approximately 100-105 km/h due to its hybrid design.
